This folder contains additional CSS tweaks that work together with the **Jellyfin Seasonals** project by CodeDevMLH.

> âš ï¸ **You need to install Jellyfin Seasonals first before using these tweaks!**
> ğŸ‘‰ [https://github.com/CodeDevMLH/Jellyfin-Seasonals](https://github.com/CodeDevMLH/Jellyfin-Seasonals)

The Jellyfin Seasonals project automatically adds seasonal animations to your Jellyfin interface based on the current date, including:
- â„ï¸ Snowflakes & Snowfall (December/January)
- ğŸ’™ Hearts (February - Valentine's Day)
- ğŸ‚ Autumn leaves (October)
- ğŸƒ Halloween (October)
- ğŸ† Fireworks (New Year)
- ğŸ… Santa & Christmas themes

**How to install Jellyfin Seasonals:**
1. Open the link above and follow the installation instructions
2. Edit the `index.html` file of your Jellyfin web instance
3. Add the seasonal container and script inside the `<body>` tag
4. Deploy the seasonals folder to your Jellyfin web directory
5. Restart Jellyfin and hard refresh your browser (Ctrl+Shift+R)

**Then apply the tweaks from this folder:**
1. Go to your Jellyfin **Admin Dashboard** in your web browser
2. Navigate to **Dashboard â†’ General â†’ Custom CSS**
3. Copy & paste the CSS from the `Jellyfin-Seasonals` folder
4. Click **Save** and hard refresh your browser
